<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 7: VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN
        BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - INSPECTION AND REPAIR - CRANKSHAFT GEAR
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CRANKSHAFT GEAR</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal</title>
            <para>Replace the crankshaft gear as follows:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place a chisel between the gear teeth and strike the chisel with a hammer to split the
                    gear.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the oil pump drive spline first to access the crankshaft gear (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600772">7.72</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Be careful not to damage the crankshaft during gear removal.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With gears removed, heat the crankshaft gear and oil pump drive spline, using
                    <emph type="bold">ZTSE4384</emph>, to 188-202&#176; C (370-395&#176; F).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the crankshaft gear first. Be sure the locating pin on the crankshaft gear
                    aligns with the crankshaft properly (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600773">7.73</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ). Press the gear into place.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the hot oil pump drive spline onto the crankshaft until flush with the
                    crankshaft gear (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure</emph>
                    <emph type="bold">
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600773">7.73</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1600772" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5224" filename="../figeg5/EG5224.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.72 Removing Oil Pump Drive Spline</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600773" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12182" filename="../figcg1/CG12182.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.73 Installing Crankshaft Gear</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
